  "prompt": "I am interested in a girl but she wants to just be friends. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings when one person wants a friendship and the other has romantic interests can be challenging. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Respect Her Wishes**: It\u2019s important to respect her decision to be just friends. Pushing for more can strain your relationship.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: If appropriate, you might express your feelings honestly to her. Let her know how you feel but emphasize that you value her friendship and are willing to respect her boundaries.\n\n3. **Self-Reflect**: Take time to understand your feelings. Why do you have romantic feelings for her, and are you willing to set them aside to maintain the friendship?\n\n4. **Give Yourself Space**: If you find it difficult to manage your feelings, it may help to take a step back for a while to gain perspective and emotional clarity.\n\n5. **Focus on Friendship**: If you decide to remain friends, focus on building a healthy friendship. Enjoy shared interests and activities, and be a supportive friend.\n\n6. **Explore New Interests**: Distracting yourself with new hobbies or meeting new people can help manage your emotions and broaden your social circle.\n\n7. **Seek Support**: If you're finding it hard, discussing your feelings with a trusted friend or counselor might be beneficial.\n\nRemember, feelings can change over time, and maintaining a positive and respectful relationship can be fulfilling in its own right.",
